label: COMPANYNAME
description: This field stores the source of the entry and provides a description for the receiver containing the originator's name.

label: COMPANTDISCRETIONARYDATA
description: This optional field stores significant codes used by originators.

label: COMPANYID
description: This field stores the originator's unique identification number.

label: STANDARDENTRYCLASSCODE
description: This field stores a character code that distinguishes the various types of ACH entries.

label: COMPANYENTRYDESCRIPTION
description: This field stores a description of the entry for the receiver.

label: EFECTIVEENTRYDATE
description: This field stores the date specified by the originator as the day on which a batch of entries is to be settled.

label: DEPOSITSETTLEMENTDATE
description: This field stores the settlement date for all originated deposits.

label: PAYSETTLEMENTDATE
description: This field stores the settlement date for all originated withdrawals.

label: IDTYPE
description: This field stores a code that specifies whether the record is used to deposit or withdraw funds by ACH Origination from the member's shares or loans.

label: ID
description: This field stores the share or loan ID.

label: EXPIRATION
description: This field stores the date used by the Purge Account Processing batch job to purge Batch ACH Origination records.

label: RECORDCHANGEDATE
description: The system stores the system date in this field when you create, change, or save the Batch ACH Origination record. Sometimes the system updates this field because the record was saved, even though there may not be any actual changes in the record.

label: ORIGAMOUNT
description: This field stores the total dollar amount of the EFT items linked to the Batch ACH Origination record through the Batch ACH Origination Number field in the EFT record.

label: GROUPNUMBER
description: This field stores the credit union-defined number used by ACH Posting to identify what items to post.

label: POSTMETHOD
description: This field store a code that specifies if the posting program should post all the ACH items together or separately.

label: STATUS
description: This field stores the status of the Batch ACH Origination record.

label: TOTALORIGINATIONCOUNT
description: This field stores the total number of ACH items included in the ACH batch.

label: TOTALPOSTEDCOUNT
description: This field stores the total number of ACH items included in the batch posting.

label: LOCATOR
description: This field stores a unique number within each member account that can be used as a unique identification of this record.
